{{Quote|They're up to no good. All those diseases in the offshoot areas&mdash;''Adascorp'' released them there!''"<br />"What?"<br />"''The company ''designed'' 'em, Jarael! Adasca's grandpa and old man wanted to put offshoots down, to drive 'em out of Arkanian society!|[[Gorman Vandrayk|Camper]] reveals to [[Jarael]] what Arkoh Adasca is planning|<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 20">[[Knights of the Old Republic 20|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 20]]</ref>}}
The '''"offshoot question"''' was the term given by genetically pure [[Arkanian/Legends|Arkanians]] to the matter over how to deal with the [[Arkanian Offshoot/Legends|offshoot]] Arkanians.<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 17">[[Knights of the Old Republic 17|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 17]]</ref> By the time of the [[Mandalorian Wars]], most had opted for segregation and relegation of the offshoots to a subjected class.<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 18">[[Knights of the Old Republic 18|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 18]]</ref> [[Arkoh Adasca]] planned to use [[The Adasca BioMechanical Corporation of Arkania|Adascorp's]] genetic engineering expertise to solve the "problem" in a generation by releasing a plague that killed them.<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 20" />

==Behind the scenes==
Author [[John Jackson Miller]] based it on such historical ethnic/religious notions as the "[[Wikipedia:Jewish Question|Jewish Question]]."<ref name="Faraway 17">{{Faraway|url=comics/swknights/swkotor17.html|text=''Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic #17''}}</ref>

